oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: History of Supply Co, 114th Field Artillery
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The 114th FA was part of the 30th Division and was composed of Tennessee National Guardsmen. The Supply Co. was responsible for providing supplies to the battery via mule drawn wagons and motorized trucks. This typed copy belonged to 1st Class Machinist Robert Jackson, Supply Co., 114th FA. It is unknown if Jackson wrote the history or if this was simply a copy provided to him. Jackson was born in Dekalb County but lived most of his life in Wilson County.
